<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>if $data passed to Zend_Controller_Action_Helper_AutoCompleteScriptaculous::prepareAutoCompletion() is empty, ie, empty string or empty array, it will return "</p>

<ul><li></li></ul><p>" as the result.</p>

<p>The problem is that the autocomplete control will treat the empty "</p>" as an actual option. Not only it is ugly but when the user presses enter the value in the text input will be wiped out, which is very irritating.

<p>The fix would be very simple, check if $data is empty, if so return nothing or an empty "</p>

<p>" pair.</p>

